track_notes: Trivial route up track. My start point was a lay-by but there is plenty of space for a car at the start of the track. Initially this is a bridle way, but the gate was locked. Watch out for Nant y Coed. It was easy to ford on my visit but perhaps not when in spate.
This was my first visit and I would avoid the ascent route and use my descent route for ascent and descent if I go again.

Total time (including ops): 3hr 45m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
